28/08/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Prime Minister Sergey Stanishev urged all members of the supreme council of the ruling Bulgarian Socialist Party (BSP) to submit asset declarations. At a meeting of BSP leaders on Saturday (26 August), Stanishev explained that the government is trying to be a leader in transparency and introduce strict rules aimed at eliminating corruption. Stanishev stressed that if the assets of BSP leaders are made public, the party would prove its determination to fight corruption. (Mediapool, news.bg, bTV - 26/08/06)
